  ﻿Register Online For 24/7 Access.


Creating an online account with Allstate gives you access to your policies anytime, anywhere. But that's not all. You can also enjoy many benefits, like:


Easy access to your ID cards 
Pay your bills online
Make changes to coverage, limits and deductibles quickly and easily 
File and track insurance claims from one convenient location 
Get access to helpful tips and tools

Register for an account
Already registered? Log in now.




Questions?
From auto insurance and home claims to payment cycles and billing—get the answers to all of our most frequently asked questions.
Browse Q&A



Billing & Account Management Made Simple.

Save time, reduce paper clutter and help the environment when you take your bills paperless today.
Need to access your insurance card? You can print a hardcopy of your card by logging in to My Account1. You can also access a digital copy of your card by downloading the free Allstate® Mobile app. Digital ID cards can be accessed at any time and presented as proof of insurance in states that accept electronic proof of insurance2.


See more ways to manage your bill



1Printing cards from your online account is not available in every state, some exceptions apply. 
2Electronic proof of insurance not accepted in every state.  Also, please note: The Allstate digital proof of insurance is not yet approved for use in NY.

Quickly Locate Documents.

Allstate makes it easy to find specific policy documents at a moment's notice. Log in to My Account to view current and past documents, or find them using the Allstate® Mobile app.
Find documents fast


Relocation Made Easy.

See how Allstate can make your move a smooth one. Visit our Moving Center to get tips and tools, and don't forget to talk to your agent about updating your policy for your new home.
Let Allstate help with your move


Manage Your Policy On The Go.

Allstate offers a number of convenient mobile apps to help assist you from wherever life takes you.
See Allstate's mobile apps


Contact Us Now.

Wondering if you should adjust your coverage? Looking for ways to save on your bill? No matter what you need, your local Allstate agent is here to help you.

To find your agent or an agent near you, click here.Or call us at 1-800-ALLSTATE (1-800-255-7828)
See more ways to contact Allstate




